In 1935,{Mr Kirkland}started work at the brewery and looked after the{ {horses.}The horses came to Shipstone's when they were 5 years old and retired when they were 20 years old. Mr. K. said the horse would{'weep when they {were distressed'.}
{Mr. Spence}remembers how much the people in{Basford}liked the horses. The women would spread ashes from the hearthfire on the roads in the winter so that the horse would not slip.
There have been lots of changes at the brewery over the years. Mr. Spence still works there and earns{109} pounds a week. He still doesn't like going into the caves, though, because of the{rats.}
